body.plain: The song is Maude Latour’s first single released after her debut studio EP, “Starsick”. The song was announced for release on May 1, 2020 via Instagram . It had also been previously teased via Instagram on March 22, 2020. On March 29, 2020, Maude teased a 40-second snippet of the track via TikTok.

annotations:
All my friends feel like they’re strangers
 I don’t wanna be famous

Sometimes, we feel overwhelmed and distant from others. This is a very common occurrence, especially for those who suffer from anxiety.
Maude continues her personal approach to songwriting as she notes these feelings and expresses how singing helps her through it all; it is her overarching passion i.e. “But I wanna sing until I drown”.

I wish that we were more like the movie
 I cry on my birthday but you would make it up to me

In these lyrics, Maude pays homage to the cult classic movie, Sixteen Candles. The end of the movie consists of Jake and Samantha meeting for the first time, as he invites her over to his house rather than to Ginny’s wedding reception. She takes him on his offer and the movie concludes with the two of them sharing a kiss over a birthday cake.

And damn, I really hate your guts
 I hate all your friends and I miss you so much
 But I blocked all your texts
This verse depicts the ironic paradox that encompasses Maude’s breakup. She is upset but still misses her ex. Despite missing him, she has blocked his number.

I mentioned that I hope we stay friends
 But I regret what I said ‘cause I heard what you told Emma

Although Maude expressed that she would like to remain amicable with her ex, she regrets being so civil after having heard that he was not so pleasant about the situation as she was.
It is clear that her ex said negative things about her to her friend – which in turn causes frustration and regret to occur after it makes its way through the grapevine and back to Maude.
Who invited you babe? ’Cause I can’t see you anymore

description.plain: Walk Backwards is a song about how blurry the line between platonic and romantic love is. This song is about the beauty and complexity of relationships, and was written specifically about Maude Latour’s best friend Morgan. Maude believes we put too much emphasis on romantic relationships, explaining she has “never felt a deeper love than [she] does with [her] best friends.”

body.plain: Walk Backwards is a song about how blurry the line between platonic and romantic love is. This song is about the beauty and complexity of relationships, and was written specifically about Maude Latour’s best friend Morgan. Maude believes we put too much emphasis on romantic relationships, explaining she has “never felt a deeper love than [she] does with [her] best friends.”

annotations:
Me and my friends do whatever we want
 And by friends I really only mean one in particular
 And that’s you
In these lines Maude is referring to her best friend Morgan, who the song is written for.

Under galaxies in the middle of the city in New York
 So, I say thanks to an unknown force

Maude also references outer space in “Ride My Bike”, singing “So, I backpack through the universe
/ And I came back with no possessions,” showcasing a common theme of space and the unknown in her music, perhaps a nod to her study of philosophy at Columbia University

Sun’s slippin’ south on the west-side
 And we still got the rest of the night
 You live east, so I walk backwards babe

Maude has said on her Tiktok (@maudelstatus): “In the summer I have a promise to see every sunset. But I live on the east side … and the sun sets in the west. So to get home I have to walk backwards to watch the sun slip… It’s about that perfect summer feeling”

And it’s only just about a quarter to nine
 You live east, so I walk backwards

Maude lives on the east side when the sun sets in the west. In the summer, she has promised to see every single sunset so as she walks home, she walks backwards so she can watch the sunset and experience that blissful, perfect summer feeling.

I know your boyfriend’s mad
 Watch you grabbin’ my hand all day
 So, I just play it cool

The original lyrics were:

I’m lyin' on your driveway
At your grandparents' house
Up state, before the weekend

In a TikTok, Maude said: “Every person I’ve dated has been jealous of our love” in reference to her best friend, Morgan.

I guess I’ll never understand
 The line between our love and romance
 ’Cause when I look at you I
 Fall right into a dream

The original lyrics were:

So the kids in Central Park
All decided to leave to go home
To get back before dark
But, they left me with you

description.plain:
Clean affixes Latour’s quick-witted musings. The upbeat, deliciously catchy alt-pop confessional encapsulates Latour’s strengths in just two minutes and thirty seconds: vividly relatable lyrics that take quick, thoughtful dips into existential territory, leaving the listener feeling both validated and intrigued.

Originally written two years before its release in 2019, Latour explains, “The difference between 19 and 21 feels paradigmatic. When I was 19, this song was earnestly me working on myself, constantly promising to clean my room and temporarily taking good care of myself in spurts. Truly, I am an extremely messy person who is constantly involved in introspection and self-improvement, epiphanies, and inner thoughts. This song has become an even truer testament to how growing is painful. Sometimes you are trying your best, and it’s still messy, and it is still your best. Growth hurts—growing pains. I’m learning so much every single day."
